snippet: The opposition leader, Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, has confirmed that she will run for a parliamentary seat in April, a spokesman for her National League for Democracy party said Tuesday.
abstract: Myanmar's opposition leader Daw Aung San Suu Kyi has confirmed that she will run for a parliamentary seat in suburban Yangon, country's largest city and her hometown.
lead_paragraph: The opposition leader, Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, has confirmed that she will run for a parliamentary seat in April, a spokesman for her National League for Democracy party said Tuesday.

headline.seo: Daw Aung San Suu Kyi To Run for Parliament in Myanmar
headline.main: Myanmar: Top Dissident to Run for Parliament
headline.print_headline: Myanmar: Top Dissident To Run for Parliament
